<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - CATERPILLAR C-10, C-12
        AND 3406E ENGINES - SERVICE BRAKE SWITCH (141)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SERVICE BRAKE SWITCH (141)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Service Brake Switch and Circuits</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0819713" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Service Brake Switch and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.28in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove conn. (141) from service brake switch. With brakes released, measure
                                    resistance to gnd. at each switch terminal (not the harness connector side).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Brake switch to gnd. at each terminal.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the brake switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With (141) removed from service brake switch, and service brakes released, measure
                                    resistance across switch terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Across switch terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the brake switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With vehicle air pressure >80 PSI, apply service brakes while measuring resistance
                                    across the brake switch terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Across switch terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the brake switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (400) from ECM and do not reconnect (141) to switch. Use test
                                    lead to jumper conn. (400) terminal 45 (circuit 97AL) to gnd. At brake switch (141),
                                    measure resistance to gnd. at circuit 97AL.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(141), 97AL to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection condition in circuit 97AL between connectors (141)
                                    and (400), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 5 (circuit 97-G) to terminal 45
                                    (circuit 97AL). Measure resistance between conn. (141) circuit 97AL and 97-GF.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(141), 97-GF to 97AL.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor conn. in circuit 97-GF, 97-GA, or 97-G between connectors
                                    (141) and (400), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With conn. (400) disconnected and jumpers removed, at (141) measure resistance
                                    between circuits 97AL and 97-GF.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(141), 97AL to 97-GF.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The brake switch and circuits check OK.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short circuit between circuit 97AL and circuit 97-GF, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
